<c74object name='av.pix.gamma.correct' category='' module=''>

    <digest>
        Convert from linear color space to sRGB
    </digest>

    <description>
        Convert from lin (linear) color space to sRGB (standard Red Green Blue). Also called gamma-correction.<br/><br/>

Useful for when processing the colors of a movie. First convert the movie to linear colorspace with expand. Then process the colors. Then convert back to sRGB colorspace with correct. Also useful when converting a full 3D generated scene to sRGB colorspace (only gamma-correction).<br/><br/>

Note: Max9 users can also use jit.fx.srgb2lin and jit.fx.lin2srgb
    </description>
    
